4 December 2008Government Communication (GCIS) will be hosting its annual Government Communicators' Awards at Emperors' Palace tomorrow.The gala evening will be addressed by the Minister in The Presidency, Dr Manto Tshabalala-Msimang, as a keynote speaker.The Government Communicators' Awards are intended to recognise improved delivery, innovation and excellence in the government communications profession. The event is attended by ministers, director-generals, communicators from all levels of government, the media, and sponsor representatives from the SABC, Standard Bank, Mercury Media, Eskom, the Three Cities group, Nestle, ITEC and Datacentrix.Members of the media are invited to cover the event: Date: Friday, 5 December 2008 (tomorrow) Time: 18:30 Venue: Emperors Palace, Kempton Park, JohannesburgRSVP Pheliswa Sebati Cell: 082 413 4609Enquiries Harold Maloka Cell: 082 847 9799Issued by: Government Communications (GCIS)